snippet.textDisplay: Hey, does anyone know what can cause one shoulder blade to raise   higher than the other? I've had this issue for about 6 months now and I feel it has something to do with a slightly torn labrum which causes my shoulder to sit further forward sometimes and pop when I raise it out to my side. But everything I've done to correct it doesnt help. My shoulders sit at equal height and I've been lifting for 3 years. So I understand how to properly engage muscles. But I've just had this nagging shoulder issue for so long and nothing seems to help. Its caused uneven muscle growth in my lats and upper chest because my shoulder doesnt seem to sit correctly and engage the tricep as much.
